  "local_port": 52262,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the types of pain during pregnancy?",
  "response": "During pregnancy, it's common to experience various types of pain and discomfort due to the physical and hormonal changes in the body. Here are some of the most common types of pain during pregnancy:\n\n### 1. **Back Pain**\n   - **Lower Back Pain:** Common due to the growing uterus, weight gain, and changes in posture.\n   - **Upper Back Pain:** Can result from breast enlargement or poor posture.\n\n### 2. **Pelvic Pain**\n   - **Round Ligament Pain:** Sharp, stabbing pain in the lower abdomen or groin, often caused by stretching of the round ligaments supporting the uterus.\n   - **Pelvic Girdle Pain (PGP):** Pain around the pelvic joint due to increased pressure on the pelvis.\n\n### 3. **Abdominal Pain**\n   - **Mild Cramping:** Similar to menstrual cramps, often harmless and caused by the uterus stretching.\n   - **Gas or Constipation Pain:** Hormonal changes can slow digestion, leading to bloating or discomfort.\n\n### 4. **Leg Pain**\n   - **Leg Cramps:** Common, especially at night, possibly due to calcium or magnesium deficiency or pressure on nerves.\n   - **Sciatica:** Pain radiating down the leg due to pressure on the sciatic nerve.\n\n### 5. **Headaches**\n   - Hormonal changes, dehydration, or stress can cause headaches during pregnancy.\n\n### 6. **Rib Pain**\n   - The expanding uterus can push against the ribs, causing discomfort or pain.\n\n### 7. **Hip Pain**\n   - Hormonal changes soften ligaments, and the growing baby can put pressure on the hips.\n\n### 8. **Braxton Hicks Contractions**\n   - Irregular, painless tightening of the uterus, known as \"practice contractions,\" which can cause mild discomfort.\n\n### 9. **Varicose Veins or Swelling**\n   - Increased blood flow and pressure on veins can cause leg pain, swelling, or discomfort.\n\n### 10. **Breast Pain**\n   - Tenderness, soreness, or swelling in the breasts due to hormonal changes.\n\n### 11. **Carpal Tunnel Syndrome**\n   - Swelling in the wrists can compress the median nerve, causing tingling, numbness, or pain in the hands.\n\n### 12. **Tailbone Pain (Coccydynia)**\n   - Pressure from the growing uterus or changes in posture can cause pain in the tailbone area.\n\n### When to Seek Medical Attention:\nWhile many types of pain are normal during pregnancy, some symptoms may indicate a serious issue. Seek immediate medical care if you experience:\n   - Severe abdominal pain or cramping.\n   - Persistent headaches or vision changes (signs of preeclampsia).\n   - Swelling in the hands or face.\n   - Pain accompanied by fever, chills, or bleeding.\n   - Any pain that feels unusual or concerning.\n\nAlways consult your healthcare provider if you're unsure about any pain or discomfort during pregnancy.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
